Note:
Runa Standard Library: String Formatting and Manipulation Utilities

Provides comprehensive string formatting and manipulation functions for Runa programs.

Idiomatic Runa code uses natural language operators:
    Let greeting be "Hello, " plus name
    Let upper_case be greeting converted to uppercase
    Let formatted be format string with template as "User {name} is {age} years old" and values as user_data

For advanced/AI-generated code, use helpers:
    Let result be concat with a as s1 and b as s2
    Let result be upper with s as text
    Let result be format_string with template as template and values as data
:End Note
Note: String Constants
Let ascii_letters be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ"
Let ascii_lowercase be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz"
Let ascii_uppercase be "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ"
Let digits be "0123456789"
Let hexdigits be "0123456789abcdefABCDEF"
Let octdigits be "01234567"
Let punctuation be "!\"#$%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?@[\\]^_`{|}~"
Let whitespace be " \t\n\r\x0b\x0c"

Note: Basic String Operations
Process called "concat" that takes a as String and b as String returns String:
    Return a plus b

Process called "upper" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return s converted to uppercase

Process called "lower" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return s converted to lowercase

Process called "title" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return s converted to title case

Process called "capitalize" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return capitalize first letter of s

Process called "swapcase" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return swap case of s

Process called "trim" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return trim whitespace from s

Process called "trim_left" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return trim whitespace from left of s

Process called "trim_right" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return trim whitespace from right of s

Process called "replace" that takes s as String and old as String and new as String returns String:
    Return replace old with new in s

Process called "replace_all" that takes s as String and old as String and new as String returns String:
    Return replace all occurrences of old with new in s

Process called "split" that takes s as String and sep as String returns List[String]:
    Return split s by sep

Process called "split_lines" that takes s as String returns List[String]:
    Return split s by newlines

Process called "split_whitespace" that takes s as String returns List[String]:
    Return split s by whitespace

Process called "join" that takes items as List[String] and sep as String returns String:
    Return join items with sep

Note: String Validation and Testing
Process called "is_empty" that takes s as String returns Boolean:
    Return length of s is equal to 0

Process called "is_blank" that takes s as String returns Boolean:
    Return trim s is empty

Process called "starts_with" that takes s as String and prefix as String returns Boolean:
    Return s starts with prefix

Process called "ends_with" that takes s as String and suffix as String returns Boolean:
    Return s ends with suffix

Process called "contains" that takes s as String and substr as String returns Boolean:
    Return substr is in s

Process called "is_alpha" that takes s as String returns Boolean:
    Return s contains only alphabetic characters

Process called "is_digit" that takes s as String returns Boolean:
    Return s contains only digits

Process called "is_alphanumeric" that takes s as String returns Boolean:
    Return s contains only alphanumeric characters

Process called "is_whitespace" that takes s as String returns Boolean:
    Return s contains only whitespace characters

Note: String Formatting
Process called "format_string" that takes template as String and values as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Let result be template
    For each key and value in values:
        Set result to replace "{" plus key plus "}" with value in result
    Return result

Process called "pad_left" that takes s as String and width as Integer and char as String (default: " ") returns String:
    Return pad s to width with char on left

Process called "pad_right" that takes s as String and width as Integer and char as String (default: " ") returns String:
    Return pad s to width with char on right

Process called "center" that takes s as String and width as Integer and char as String (default: " ") returns String:
    Return center s in width with char

Process called "justify_left" that takes s as String and width as Integer returns String:
    Return justify s to left in width

Process called "justify_right" that takes s as String and width as Integer returns String:
    Return justify s to right in width

Process called "justify_center" that takes s as String and width as Integer returns String:
    Return justify s to center in width

Note: String Analysis
Process called "count" that takes s as String and substr as String returns Integer:
    Return count occurrences of substr in s

Process called "find" that takes s as String and substr as String returns Integer:
    Return find first occurrence of substr in s

Process called "find_last" that takes s as String and substr as String returns Integer:
    Return find last occurrence of substr in s

Process called "index_of" that takes s as String and substr as String returns Integer:
    Return index of first occurrence of substr in s

Process called "last_index_of" that takes s as String and substr as String returns Integer:
    Return index of last occurrence of substr in s

Note: String Transformation
Process called "reverse" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return reverse s

Process called "repeat" that takes s as String and count as Integer returns String:
    Return repeat s count times

Process called "substring" that takes s as String and start as Integer and end as Integer returns String:
    Return substring of s from start to end

Process called "remove" that takes s as String and substr as String returns String:
    Return remove substr from s

Process called "remove_all" that takes s as String and substr as String returns String:
    Return remove all occurrences of substr from s

Note: String Encoding and Escaping
Process called "escape_html" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return escape html entities in s

Process called "unescape_html" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return unescape html entities in s

Process called "escape_regex" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return escape regex special characters in s

Process called "quote" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return quote s with double quotes

Process called "unquote" that takes s as String returns String:
    Return unquote s by removing surrounding quotes

Note: String Templates
Class StringTemplate with:
    template as String

    Process called "substitute" that takes self and values as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
        Return format_string with template as self.template and values as values

    Process called "safe_substitute" that takes self and values as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
        Let result be self.template
        For each key and value in values:
            Set result to replace "$" plus key with value in result
        Return result

Note: String Builder for Efficient Concatenation
Class StringBuilder with:
    parts as List[String]

    Process called "append" that takes self and s as String returns StringBuilder:
        Add s to self.parts
        Return self

    Process called "append_line" that takes self and s as String returns StringBuilder:
        Add s plus newline to self.parts
        Return self

    Process called "build" that takes self returns String:
        Return join self.parts with ""

    Process called "clear" that takes self returns StringBuilder:
        Set self.parts to list containing
        Return self

    Process called "length" that takes self returns Integer:
        Let total be 0
        For each part in self.parts:
            Set total to total plus length of part
        Return total 